Package com.univpm.po.NutritionStats.service.statistic

Class Statistic

java.lang.Object
com.univpm.po.NutritionStats.service.statistic.Statistic
Direct Known Subclasses:
Correlation, Mean, Percentage, StandardDeviation
public abstract class Statistic extends Object
Statistic is an abstract class that will be instantiated with its subclasses which are all the type of statistic that can be calculated on a provided filtered diary.

The supported statistics are the following:

•Sample mean about all nutrition type,

•Sample standard deviation about all nutrition type,

•Percentage values about caloric intake,

•Correlation between calories and weight tendency.

Author:
Davide Mazzatenta

  • Field Details

    • statsValues

      protected Map<AllNutrientNonNutrient,Float> statsValues
      An HashMap containing a Float value for each nutrient type. The meaning of the Values depends on the subclass which assign those Values. For example, the subclass Mean will put the value of the sample mean.
